2026-03-29T13:35:50.3825371Z               "id": "97459c7d94a9f7b1ba375eab62c26adb4b778dba",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3828098Z               "message": "Fix device types: use physical archetype instead of per-service types\n\nPreviously, each Hue service endpoint (motion, temperature, battery,\nconnectivity) created separate Device rows with service-specific types.\nA single physical motion sensor would get DeviceType \"motion_sensor\",\n\"battery\", or \"zigbee_connectivity\" depending on which service created\nit first. Stale device removal was also per-type, missing cross-type\ndevices.\n\nNow: one Device row per physical Hue device, with DeviceType set from\nthe Hue device archetype (e.g. \"motion_sensor\"). All reading types\n(motion, temperature, battery, connectivity) attach to the same device.\nStale removal is a single pass across all service types.\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01Gmjk912cuixJo7D9UqZQGA",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3830745Z               "timestamp": "2026-03-29T12:05:17Z",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3831060Z               "tree_id": "a23e7285e29a338abd854160c68b95b7eea24bc5",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3831547Z               "url": "https://github.com/***/hpoll/commit/97459c7d94a9f7b1ba375eab62c26adb4b778dba"
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3832227Z             },
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3832561Z             {
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3832859Z               "author": {
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3833230Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3833901Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3834311Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3834698Z               },
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3835015Z               "committer": {
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3835422Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3835874Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3836278Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3836625Z               },
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3836817Z               "distinct": false,
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3837087Z               "id": "b37163e189963ac8a6e625b4c1680c52a19941d7",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3840672Z               "message": "Derive device type from Hue services array, not metadata archetype\n\nThe Hue API metadata.archetype field only covers lighting form factors\n(e.g. \"classic_bulb\", \"spot_bulb\") and returns \"unknown_archetype\" for\nsensors. Using it as DeviceType would break queries that filter by\n\"motion_sensor\".\n\nInstead, derive the device type from the device's services[] array:\nif it has an rtype \"motion\" service → motion_sensor, \"temperature\" →\ntemperature_sensor, otherwise → unknown. This correctly identifies\nphysical motion sensors regardless of their Hue archetype.\n\nUpdated test mock devices to use realistic \"unknown_archetype\" values\n(matching what real Hue motion sensors report) to verify the\nservices-based derivation works correctly.\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01Gmjk912cuixJo7D9UqZQGA",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3843629Z               "timestamp": "2026-03-29T12:10:39Z",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3844368Z               "tree_id": "3999893010f4273ad83bc2baaf250e12df118034",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3844899Z               "url": "https://github.com/***/hpoll/commit/b37163e189963ac8a6e625b4c1680c52a19941d7"
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3845296Z             },
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3845482Z             {
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3845660Z               "author": {
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3845892Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3846162Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3846394Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3846613Z               },
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3846798Z               "committer": {
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3847037Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3847292Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3847514Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3847732Z               },
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3847908Z               "distinct": false,
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3848176Z               "id": "b1cc937d44d921b69aebbddf9c9919c16b642d15",
2026-03-29T13:35:50.3849886Z               "message": "Only run stale device removal when all endpoints are polled\n\nOn non-battery poll cycles, only motion and temperature endpoints are\nqueried. Devices that only appear in battery/connectivity (lights,\nplugs, switches) would not be in allCurrentDeviceIds and would be\nincorrectly removed as stale. Now stale removal only runs when\nshouldPollBattery is true, ensuring we have the complete picture.\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01Gmjk912cuixJo7D9UqZQGA",
